# Windows Dev Environment

Primary dev path: **PowerShell native + Docker Desktop + uv + GNU Make (GnuWin32)**. No WSL2 shell. No Unix-only paths.

## Absolute rules

- **Never** hardcode OS paths: no `.local/bin/uv`, no `/Users/...`, no `~/...`
- Invoke tools by name on PATH: `uv`, `python`, `docker`, `make`, `pytest`
- Makefile must work with **GnuWin32 Make** — avoid bash-only syntax (`$(shell ...)`, heredocs, `&&` chains in complex recipes)
- `.gitattributes` enforces **LF** line endings on all text files

## Standard commands

```powershell
make install      # uv sync --all-packages --group dev
make docker-up    # Postgres 16 + Redis 7
make test         # pytest
make api          # FastAPI on :8000
```

## Python version

Pinned **3.11** via `.python-version`. Never use 3.12+ features. Range: `>=3.11,<3.12`.

## Docker

- Compose file at repo root; init SQL mounted from `infra/postgres/init.sql`
- **Postgres host port 5433** (container 5432) — avoids conflict with local PostgreSQL on Windows
- If `docker compose up` fails with pipe error → Docker Desktop is not running; ask user to start it

## README

Windows/PowerShell is the **documented default** setup path. Other OS notes are secondary.
